        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Exodus 37</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                        <l n="1">And Bezalel made the ark of acacia wood:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            two cubits and a half the length of it, and a cubit
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            and a half the breadth of it, and a cubit and a half the height of
                            it.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                        <l n="2">And he overlaid it with pure gold inside and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            out, and made a moulding of gold for it around it.</l>
                        <l n="3">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            he <supplied reason="lost">cast</supplied> for it four rings of gold
                            four on the corners of it,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            and two rings on the one side of it, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            two rings on the second side of it.</l>
                        <l n="4">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            he made poles of acacia wood and overlaid them with gold.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                        <l n="5">And he put the poles into the rings
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            on the sides of the ark, to carry
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            the ark.</l>
                        <l n="6">And he made the cover of pure gold:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            two cubits and a half the length of it, and one cubit and a half the
                                <supplied reason="lost">breadth</supplied> of it.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                        <l n="7">And he made two cherubim of gold, he made them of hammered work,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            on the two ends of the cover.</l>
                        <l n="8">One cherub on the end
                            <milestone unit="page" n="150v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            on this side, and one cherub on this side. He made
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            the cherubim from the cover on the two ends of it.</l>
                        <l n="9">And the cherubim
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            spread out their wings above, encircling the cover with their wings,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            with their faces one to another:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            the faces of the cherubim were toward the cover.</l>
                        <l n="10">And he made the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            table of acacia wood: two cubits the length of it, and a cubit
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            the breadth of it, and a cubit and a half the height of it.</l>
                        <l n="11">And he overlaid
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            it with pure gold, and made for it a moulding of gold around it.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                        <l n="12">And he made for it a border |of| a hand|breadth| around it, and he made
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            a moulding of gold for the border all around.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                        <l n="13">And he cast for it four rings of gold, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            put the rings on the four corners that
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            are at its four legs.</l>
                        <l n="14">Opposite to the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            border were the rings, the places for the poles to
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            carry the table. <seg type="commented" n="#seg001" /><addSpan
                                spanTo="#add001" /><supplied reason="lost">The</supplied>
                            <emph>verse ‘And he made the poles’ </emph><supplied reason="lost">is
                                missing here</supplied>.<anchor xml:id="add001" /><anchor
                                type="commented" xml:id="seg001" /><ref target="#fn1"
                                type="noteAnchor" /></l>
                        <l n="15"><addSpan spanTo="#add002" /><emph>And he made</emph>
                            <supplied reason="lost">the</supplied>
                            <emph>poles of acacia wood, </emph><supplied reason="lost">and
                                overlaid</supplied>
                            <emph>them with</emph>
                            <supplied reason="lost">gold, to</supplied><emph> carry the
                                table</emph>.<anchor xml:id="add002" /></l>
                        <l n="16">And he made the vessels
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            which were on the table: its bowls <seg type="commented" n="#seg002"
                             />in which
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            they baked the showbread, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            its spoons with which the priest measured the incense,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            and its cloths |used for covering the showbread|, and its <supplied
                                reason="lost">†tablecloths</supplied><ref target="#fn2"
                                type="noteAnchor" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            on which were the cloths <seg type="commented" n="#seg003" />with which
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            adjacent breads were separated<anchor type="commented" xml:id="seg003"
                                 /><ref target="#fn3" type="noteAnchor" /> so that there would be
                            airflow between<ref target="#fn4" type="noteAnchor" /> them,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="151r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            so that they would not go mouldy. He made all the vessels of pure
                                gold.<anchor type="commented" xml:id="seg002" /><ref target="#fn5"
                                type="noteAnchor" /></l>
                        <l n="17">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            And he made the lampstand of pure gold. He made the lampstand of
                            hammered work:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            its shaft, and its branch; its cups, its knobs,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            and its leaves were of the one same |piece|.</l>
                        <l n="18">And six
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            branches were going out of the sides of it, three branches of the lampstand
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            out of one side, and three branches of the lampstand out of the second
                            side,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                        <l n="19">Three cups coupled, a knob and a leaf in one branch,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            and three cups coupled, with a knob and a leaf in one branch,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            so for the six branches that come out of the lampstand,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                        <l n="20">And <delSpan spanTo="#del001" />three<anchor xml:id="del001" />
                            <addSpan spanTo="#add003" /><emph>four</emph><anchor xml:id="add003" />
                            cups coupled in the lampstand,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            their knobs and their leaves,</l>
                        <l n="21">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            a knob under the two branches of the one same piece, and a knob
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            under the two branches of the one same piece, and a knob
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            under the two branches of the one same piece, for the six branches
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            coming out of it.</l>
                        <l n="22">Their knobs
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            and their branches were of the same piece, all of it was one hammered
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            work of pure gold.</l>
                        <l n="23">And he made its seven places for candles,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            and its tongs, and their censers of pure
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            gold.</l>
                        <l n="24">He made it and all its vessels of a kantar of pure gold.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                        <l n="25">And he made the incense altar
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            of acacia wood: a cubit the length of it, and
                            <milestone unit="page" n="151v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            a cubit the breadth of it, <addSpan spanTo="#add004"
                                 /><emph>foursquare</emph><anchor xml:id="add004" />, and two cubits
                            the height of it,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            the horns of it were of one piece with it.</l>
                        <l n="26">And he overlaid it with pure gold:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            the top of it and the sides of it all around, and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            horns of it. And he made a moulding of gold for it all around.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                        <l n="27">And he made two rings of gold for it under
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            its moulding on the two sides of it, on the two corners of it,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            the places for the poles to carry it with them.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                        <l n="28">And he made the poles of acacia wood,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            and overlaid them with gold.</l>
                        <l n="29">And he made the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            holy anointing oil, and the pure incense of sweet spices,
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="line-11-1" n="11" next="ADub.III.73.002.038.trl.xml#line-11-2" />
                            the work of apothecary.</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="fn1" type="footnote">Inserted by another hand in
                            Hebrew.</note>
                        <note xml:id="fn2" type="footnote">An uncertain translation of
                                <emph>stolpec</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="fn3" type="footnote">Lit. ‘with which it was covered between
                            every bread’.</note>
                        <note xml:id="fn4" type="footnote">Lit. ‘through among’.</note>
                        <note xml:id="fn5" type="footnote">Interpretative translation.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
